tcm described the impact and the influence of the movie :   cultural impact the film marked the rock and roll revolution by featuring bill haley & his comets ' " rock around the clock " , initially a b - side , over the film 's opening credits ( with a lengthy drum solo introduction , unlike the originally released single ) , as well as in the first scene , in an instrumental version in the middle of the film , and at the close of the movie , establishing that song as an instant hit .

rock songs : this bill haley number was only a minor hit until featured in the movie " blackboard jungle "

" rock around the clock "